title: Siberian husky puppy missing after burglary
text:
NEW YORK (AP) - New York City police say a Siberian husky puppy is missing after a Bronx apartment was burglarized.
Police say the owner returned home on Tuesday to find the front door lock broken.
They say the apartment was in disarray and the tenant's female puppy named "Luna" was missing.
Also missing was $1,000 in cash, numerous pairs of Air Jordan sneakers and electronic equipment.
Police are asking for the public's help in identifying the suspect.
